<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>The Snowman is an import exclusive and import friendly with English and Japanese options for sampling the finer aspects of Raymond Brigg's Snowman creation. Includes some enjoyable mini games to embellish flying through the sky with a gaggle of rotund snowmen.
                  <br><br>One winter morning a little boy named James wakes up to find that everything outside has turned snow-white. Overjoyed, James rushes downstairs and into the garden, where he begins to build a snowman. James sleeps fitfully, and at midnight he wakes up and decides to check on his snowman. He opens the back door... he can't believe his eyes... The snowman has come to life! James finds himself face to face with a smiling snowman, who with a polite doff of his hat introduces himself and marks the beginning of magical friendship and marvellous adventure
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
			<br>Software which can play familiar with the "snowman" in the picture book. And it is moving the snowman in the mini-games or cool of seven, and be able to read the snowman, watch the snowman in the full uncut animation video in the narrated picture book by actress Keiko Takeshita, content and dying snowman fan.
			<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Christmas & Fantasy themes.</li></ul></td>
	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

